Running multi-rank ring_test benchmark with correctness checks
=========================================================
Config: world_size=2, methods=['pytorch', 'fa2', 'fa3', 'min_varlen', 'min_varlen_ring', 'min_varlen_mega_ring'], B=16, seqlen=512,1024,2048,4096,8192, qhead=32, kvhead=8, D=128, mode=both, num_comp_sm=128, num_comm_sm=4, warmup=20, iters=30, check=True
Checks compare each rank output against a full-rank PyTorch reference.
Causal checks use the zigzag [front | back] reference by default.
Agg TFLOPS sums visible attention work across ranks; Avg/GPU is that value divided by world_size.

